                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Which is better: CA or MBA in Finance?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Both have distinct advantages. CA provides deep technical expertise in accounting, taxation, and audit with excellent job security and independent practice opportunities. MBA Finance offers broader business knowledge, leadership skills, and faster corporate growth. CA is more specialized and cost-effective, while MBA opens doors to senior management roles. Your choice should depend on your career goals, interests, and preferred work environment.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        How difficult is it to clear CA exams?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>CA exams are challenging but achievable with proper preparation and dedication. The pass rates are typically 10-15% for each level, but this reflects the high standards rather than impossibility. Success requires consistent study (4-6 hours daily), good coaching, regular practice, and strong conceptual understanding. Many students clear on their first attempt with proper planning and effort.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Can I work while pursuing CA?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes, during articleship (practical training), you work with a CA firm while preparing for CA Final. This provides hands-on experience and a stipend. However, balancing work and studies requires excellent time management. Many students also take up part-time work or freelance assignments during their preparation phase to gain experience and earn income.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
