                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Is mathematics important for accounting and finance?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Basic mathematics is essential, but you don't need advanced calculus or complex mathematics. Focus on arithmetic, percentages, ratios, basic statistics, and financial mathematics (compound interest, present value, etc.). Most accounting work involves logical thinking and systematic approaches rather than complex mathematical calculations. Software tools handle most computational work.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
